description: Boston Philharmonic Youth Orchestra Iniciada la función el ingreso del publico demorado esta sujeto al programa: Benjamin Zander, director La Orquesta Filarmónica Juvenil de Boston (BPYO) se formó en 2012 bajo los auspicios de la Filarmónica de Boston. Dirigida por Benjamin Zander, tiene como lema: ?Forjando futuros líderes mediante la música?. Los 120 integrantes de la BPYO tienen un rango de edades entre 12 y 21 años, lo cual permite a los más jóvenes colaborar con estudiantes mayores que ya comienzan sus carreras profesionales. La BPYO ofrece una oportunidad única a jóvenes músicos para estudiar el gran repertorio orquestal dentro de una dinámica comunidad musical e intelectualmente estimulante. En 2019 la Orquesta fue nombrada Mejor Ensamble de Música Clásica por la Boston Magazine. En su temporada inaugural 2012-2013 tocó dos conciertos en la Boston Symphony Hall y emprendió una gira por cuatro ciudades en Países Bajos.

title: Orquesta Sinfónica Juvenil Silvestre Revueltas
description: En el marco celebratorio por los primeros 20 años de su creación, la Orquesta Sinfónica Juvenil Silvestre Revueltas presentará un programa conformado por dos efemérides musicales de relevancia internacional. Interpretarán la obertura de la ópera El murciélago, de Richard Strauss II, en ocasión del bicentenario del fallecimiento del prolífico músico austriaco, cuya extensa obra abarca valses, polkas, marchas y cuadrillas que retratan a la sociedad vienesa del siglo XIX. Asimismo, presentarán la Sinfonía no. 10 de Dmitri Shostakóvich, la cual evoca sentimientos tan disímiles como tragedia, desesperación, terror y triunfo, y que ha sido "traducida" como una representación de los años del régimen de Stalin en Rusia, rememorando los millones de personas fallecidas bajo su régimen. Obra interpretada en conmemoración por el 50° aniversario luctuoso del compositor ruso.

description: La orQuesTa filArmónicA de La DIVERSIDAD, es un proyecto que surge de la imperante necesidad de crear y resguardar un espacio seguro, de visibilidad, de vulnerabilidad y de confianza para las, les, los músic(as, ques, os) pertenecientes a todo el amplio espectro de los que conformamos la diversidad sexo/afectiva y grupxs vulneradxs aliadxs. El quehacer artístico requiere para sí un entorno en el cual se puedan desenvolver los individuos con total libertad, sin prejuicios, donde pueda desarrollar su identidad, un espacio donde confluyan y cooperen todas las letras de la diversidad en pos de un desarrollo artístico más íntegro. Somos la primera de nuestro tipo en Latinoamérica. Desde el 2024 consolidamos redes de cooperación entre los músicos LGBTQIA+ de toda la república y buscamos extenderlas a nivel internacional en un mediano plazo. SOMOS LIBRES, SOMOS DIVERSES, SOMOS LA OFIDI.

description: The original film is on the big screen with a live orchestra. Recharge your flux capacitor...and get ready to celebrate the 40th Anniversary of BACK TO THE FUTURE. The 1.21-gigawatt blockbuster topped the 1985 box office chart, spawned two wildly successful sequels and stamped an enduring imprint on pop culture. Join Marty McFly, Doc Brown and a time traveling DeLorean for the adventure of a lifetime as they travel to the past, present and future, setting off a time-shattering chain reaction that disrupts the space-time continuum! Experience the thrill of Back to the Future like never before ?on a big hi-def screen accompanied by the South Florida Symphony Orchestra performing Alan Silvestri's dazzling musical score live in sync with the movie. Time travel starts the moment you arrive! Before the orchestra takes you Back to the Future, party like it's 1985 with a real DeLorean photo op, classic 80s arcade games, and a rad soundtrack of the decade's greatest hits.

description: May the Fourth be with you! This must-experience outdoor concert features the Nashville Symphony conducted by Enrico Lopez-Yañez performing John Williams - and other composers - iconic scores. It' is the memorable music from a galaxy far far away featuring Star Wars selections from the entire film saga, including some of the most thrilling music ever written for movies. Highlights include the Star Wars Main Title, The Imperial March (Darth Vader's Theme), The Phantom Menace Suite, The Rise of Skywalker: The Speeder Chase, and so much more.

title: Shrek 2 in Concert - Grand Rapids Symphony
description: The most successful film in this beloved animation franchise, Shrek 2 features the vocal talents of Mike Myers, Cameron Diaz, Eddie Murphy, Antonio Banderas, John Cleese and Julie Andrews, along with an enchanting orchestral score by acclaimed composer Harry Gregson-Williams. In this installment, Shrek and Princess Fiona return from their honeymoon to find an invitation to visit Fiona?s parents, the King and Queen of the Kingdom of Far, Far Away, forcing Shrek to face his greatest challenge yet... the in-laws! Little do Shrek and Fiona know that their marriage foiled the King?s plans for his daughter?s future... and his own. Now he must enlist the help of a powerful Fairy Godmother, the handsome Prince Charming and the famed ogre killer Puss In Boots to restore his own version of ?happily ever after?. Family fun for kids of all ages, Shrek 2 in Concert will make all of your musical fairytales come true! Shrek 2 © 2025 DreamWorks Animation LLC. All Rights Reserved.

organizer: Oz-Sino Association for Advancement of Culture & Arts Inc
description: Approximate Running Times: Doors - TBC Start - 7:30pm Finish - TBC The Yellow River Cantata Under the baton of renowned Chinese conductor Cao Ding, "Voices for Peace" brings together nearly 200 singers from local Chinese choirs, acclaimed soprano Ke Lvwa, and celebrated baritone Christian Haotian Qi. The concert's second half features The Yellow River Cantata - a powerful choral masterpiece by Xian Xinghai and Guang Weiran - honouring the strength, unity, and resilience of the Chinese people. The first half showcases world-famous classics, opera highlights, group and children's choir performances. Blending Chinese themes with Western musical techniques, this commemorative event marks 80 years since the end of World War II. Through passionate expression and rich harmonies, this concert stands as a heartfelt tribute to the past and a call to preserve peace for generations to come.

title: Evangelion Wind Symphony
description: To celebrate Neon Genesis Evangelion's 30th anniversary, Evangelion Wind Symphony 2025 is coming to Toronto this August! For the first time ever in North America, Yoko Takahashi, the legendary voice behind one of anime's most iconic songs, A Cruel Angel's Thesis, will join the tour. The concert will showcase iconic songs from the series, featuring special performances by Yoko Takahashi, making it an unforgettable experience for long-time fans. Adding to this special edition, newly arranged wind orchestra pieces from Evangelion: 3.0+1.0 Thrice Upon a Time will be performed live for the first time, alongside beloved classics from the original TV series and Rebuild of Evangelion films. With the grandeur and intensity of a full wind orchestra, this immersive concert promises to be an unforgettable experience for fans. Special surprise: The first 1,000 ticket buyers in each city will receive a limited edition Evangelion badge at the concert, which will unlock a secret surprise.

title: John Pizzarelli Trio (Early)
description: Guitarist and singer JOHN PIZZARELLI has been hailed by the Boston Globe for reinvigorating the Great American Songbook and re-popularizing jazz. Established as one of the prime contemporary interpreters of the Great American Songbook, Pizzarelli has expanded that repertoire by including the music of Paul McCartney, Joni Mitchell, Neil Young, Tom Waits, Antnio Carlos Jobim and the Beatles. In addition to being a bandleader and solo performer, Pizzarelli has been a special guest on recordings for major pop names such as Natalie Cole, Kristin Chenoweth, Tom Wopat, Rickie Lee Jones and Dave Van Ronk, as well as leading jazz artists such as Rosemary Clooney, Ruby Braff, Johnny Frigo, Buddy DeFranco, Harry Allen and, of course, his father Bucky Pizzarelli. He won a Grammy Award in the Best Traditional Pop Vocal Album category as co-producer of James Taylors American Standard in 2021. A radio personality who got his start in the medium in 1984, Pizzarelli is co-host, alongside wife Jessica Molaskey, of Radio Deluxe with John Pizzarelli. He has performed on Americas most popular national television shows such as The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon, Conan, and Great Performances, as well as the talk shows of Jay Leno, David Letterman, Regis Philbin and the Macys Thanksgiving Day Parade.

title: Songs of Peace and Remembrance
description: Running Times: Doors: 7:00pm Start: 7:30pm Finish: 9:30pm Internationally acclaimed artists from the Shenyang Conservatory of Music make their Australian debut with a vibrant program of Chinese classical & traditional music, featuring folk, vocal & instrumental works including On the Songhua River, Ode to the Yellow River & Nanniwan. A distinguished lineup of internationally acclaimed virtuosos, renowned vocalists & award-winning talents from the Shenyang Conservatory of Music, one of China's most prestigious institutions, makes its momentous Australian debut with a captivating program of Chinese classical and traditional music. Uniting world-class artistry with deep cultural resonance, this concert is a breathtaking celebration of musical excellence. It offers a powerful reflection on memory, resilience & renewal-an evocative tribute to the past and a moving call for peace through the universal language of music, marking 80 years since the end of World War II.

title: Max Richter: Sleep - 10 Year Anniversary
description: The all-night performances of 'SLEEP' have become distinctive cultural events that challenge how we experience music; blurring the lines between concert and art installation and taking place in the world's most iconic settings such as the Sydney Opera House, Philharmonie de Paris and The Great Wall of China. The milestone tenth anniversary this September will see Richter bring this transcendental live experience to new audiences by playing the largest SLEEP shows to date at Alexandra Palace in London on Friday 5th & Saturday 6th September. This will mark the first time Richter has performed 'SLEEP' in London since 2017. Please note this is an overnight show with a bed provided as well as a light breakfast. Specific bedding is allocated during the ticket purchase process. Beds cannot be switched. Upon entry, please find your allocated bed and get comfy, ready for the show. description: Music Director Nurhan Arman leads the orchestra in a program drenched in melody. One of Mendelssohn's brilliant string symphonies opens the concert, followed by the return of a spectacular virtuoso who thrilled Sinfonia Toronto listeners in 2021. Grandson of the legendary Soviet violinist Viktor Pikayzen, violinist Igor Pikayzen completed degrees at Yale and Juilliard, won numerous international competitions and has performed with major orchestras around the world. He joins Sinfonia Toronto for Shostakovch's gripping Sonata for Violin with String Orchestra and Timpani. After intermission the orchestra will play one of the most beloved works of the Romantic repertoire, the famous Serenade Dvorak wrote with great joy during the ecstatic early years of his marriage.

title: Dennis James Hosts Halloween
description: It's not officially Halloween until Bloomington's favorite musical mastermind, Dennis James, returns for his annual spooky performance. Dennis James Hosts Halloween returns, as the legendary cinema organist and IU graduate provides the soundtrack to a silent film and a live radio reenactment. The live onstage portrayal of an old-time radio thriller titled Waxworks will kick off the evening and will be performed by actors, including students from IU's Department of Theatre, Drama, and Contemporary Dance, as James plays the soundtrack on IU Auditorium's 4,532-pipe organ. This episode comes from a classic radio series titled Suspense, which was one of the most popular and successful radio programs during its run of over 900 episodes, spanning 1946-1962. James will conclude the evening with the backing soundtrack to a screening of a 1924 German silent horror film also titled Waxworks that ties three stories together in an anthology format with the final segment featuring Jack the Ripper.

title: Danae Döerken
description: The Greek-German pianist Danae Doerken belongs to the elite of internationally sought-after artists of a new generation who captivates audiences and fellow musicians alike with her breathtaking technique, extraordinary stage presence and musical depth. Songs and Images explores works inspired by the sounds and sights that shaped their composers. Schumann's Forest Scenes are short musical depictions of nine settings he experienced when walking through the forest, while Schubert's Fantasy Op. 15 is based on his own famous song "Der Wanderer" that speaks about trying to find happiness. Debussy captures three vivid impressions in sound, while Bartok's Romanian Folk Dances were influenced by folk tunes that he heard on the street. The program ends with two famous works by Liszt, his Love Dream No. 3 and his Rigoletto-Paraphrase, weaving together four operatic themes from his opera "Rigoletto", singing together in harmonious unity.

description: Child Policy: This performance is not suitable for children under six years old. Children under the age of 16 must be accompanied by an adult at all APO events. Conductor Giordano Bellincampi Cello Daniel Müller-Schott Schubert Rosamunde: Overture Schumann Cello Concerto Beethoven The Creatures of Prometheus: selection Est. running time one hour and 45 minutes including a 20-minute interval Beethoven's only full-length ballet, The Creatures of Prometheus, is set to a story on a theme close to its composer's heart - the civilising power of art. The titular creatures whom Prometheus brings to life represent humanity itself, and Beethoven responded to the story of their enlightenment with engaging, sunny music. Daniel Muller-Schott, one of the world's outstanding cellists, plays Schumann's introspective, contemplative concerto. To open, Giordano Bellincampi conducts Schubert's genial overture.

title: The Music of Hans Zimmerman & Others - A Celebration of Film Music
description: No other composer has influenced the film world in the past two decades as much as the Oscar-, Globe- and Emmy-winning composer Hans Zimmer with his staggering compositions for films such as "James Bond", "The Lion King", "Pirates of the Caribbean", "Gladiator", "The Dark Knight", "Man of Steel", "Inception", and "Interstellar". Hans Zimmer wrote the film scores of more than 200 movies, won his second Oscar for "Dune" (2022), following his first Academy Award for "The Lion King" (1994). He named Ennio Morricone as his idol and role-model, whose work will be featured with excerpts from the films "The Good, the Bad and the Ugly" and "Once Upon a Time in the West". Zimmer followed Morricone's example of composing the film music often before (instead of after) filming, and shaped the entire film. He changed the beginning of Ridley Scott's "Gladiator" for example, and the world-famous director moved into the studio of Hans Zimmer.

title: Valencia Baryton Project
description: The Valencia Baryton Project is a dynamic ensemble reimagining the forgotten sound of the baryton, an 18th-century string instrument blending bowed and plucked strings. Founded by barytonist Matthew Baker, the group also features violist Máté Szücs and cellist David Apellániz. Together, they revive Haydn's 123 trios and other works written for baryton, viola and cello, while expanding the repertoire through modern commissions. The trio has performed across Europe and the Americas, earning acclaim for their inventive programming and polished sound. Their recordings on Naxos have received international praise, bringing new life to what was once considered the pinnacle of aristocratic instruments.

title: Royal Philharmonic Orchestra w/Ray Chen, conducted by Vasily Petrenko
description: Founded in 1946 by Sir Thomas Beecham, The Royal Philharmonic Orchestra was given the title 'Royal' by the Queen in 1966, confirming its irreplaceable position in the British music world. Throughout its history, the Royal Philharmonic Orchestra has attracted and collaborated with some of the most inspirational artists, including Rudolf Kempe, Antal Doráti, Walter Weller, André Previn, Vladimir Ashkenazy, and many others. Vladimir Ashkenazy,Yuri Temirkanov and Daniele Gatti have all been Principal Conductors of the Orchestra, and in August 2021,Vasily Petrenko became the new Music Director. This is a landmark appointment in the history of the Royal Philharmonic Orchestra and Vasily Petrenko's first two seasons with the Royal Philharmonic Orchestra have been well received by audiences and critics alike.

description: Après une tournée en Europe avec « Les 4 sans voix », Steeve Diamond est de retour sur scène avec un nouveau spectacle. Inspiré du succès de « Les 3 ténors de l'humour », il vous présente Bocelli & Friends. Un spectacle unique en son genre, qui allie chansons, humour et imitations. Imaginez nos plus grands chanteurs québécois et internationaux partageant la scène avec le légendaire ténor italien Andrea Bocelli, interprétant Ordinaire de Robert Charlebois, The Prayer de Céline Dion et You Are So Beautiful de Joe Cocker, accompagné de l'iconique Maria Callas. Parmi les nombreux invités, on retrouve Ginette Reno, Zucchero, Judy Garland, Gerry Boulet, Kenny Rogers, Joe Cocker, Jean-Pierre Ferland, Céline Dion, Claude Dubois, Chris Stapleton, Diane Dufresne, Frank Sinatra, Maria Callas, et bien d'autres encore.

title: Harry Potter And The Prisoner of Azkaban In Concert
organizer: Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban™ in Concert
description: First a bestseller, then a major movie, now a magical concert event: CineConcerts presents Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban in Concert. Experience the adventures of your favorite wizard all over again set to the music of a live symphony orchestra. Get ready to encounter a Dementor, rider the Knight Bus and discover just who Sirius Black really is.

title: Songs from the Heart
description: Sinfonia Toronto presents a wonderfully varied program of music from three eras and from Canada, England, France and Vienna. Maestro Arman leads the orchestra in Elgar's lyrical Serenade, the world premiere of a folk-inspired Sinfonietta by Montreal composer Petros Shoujounian, the first performance of Toronto composer Colin Eatock's beautiful settings of poems by Bengali literary icon Rabindrath Tagore, a famous Romantic solo violin showpiece and a lush orchestral version of Beethoven's famous Pathétique sonata. Two exciting young Canadian soloists will be presented - soprano Kripa Nageshwar will perform the Eatock songs, and violinist Evan Pyne will appear in Saint-Saëns' brilliant Romantic virtuoso show-stopper, the Introduction and Rondo Capriccioso.

title: Strings and Winds : Tucson Symphony Orchestra
description: Musicians from the Tucson Symphony Orchestra The TSO string quartet and wind quintet come together to feature music of Dvorák, Barber, and Valerie Coleman.

title: Yo Yo Ma w/ Minnesota Orchestra
Lords of the Sound: The Lord of the Rings in Concert
description: In a groundbreaking performance the renowned International Ukrainian symphony orchestra Lords of the Sound is bringing its iconic concert The Lord of the Rings in Concert to the USA. The Lord of the Rings in Concert transports audiences to Middle earth, capturing the essence of Howard Shores Oscar winning soundtrack from The Lord of the Rings trilogy. His music will resonate with a new strength as Lords of the Sound brings it to life on stage. Lords of the Sound promises a musical experience that captures the depth heroism and timelessness of Shores work. The concert is an adventure across Middle earth an enchanting journey through one of cinemas most epic soundtracks. With almost every classical instrument on stage Lords of the Sound maintains its symphonic roots while embracing contemporary elements including electronic instruments to offer an unforgettable experience.
location: New York, United States Of America

title: Lords Of The Sound: The Music of Hans Zimmer
Lords Of The Sound Orchestra: The Music of Hans Zimmer
Piano Heist
description: In 2022, lifelong friends Nico Rhodes and Patrick Courtin were taken aback by the stark realization that the piano had fallen out of favour. Determined to restore its luster and reclaim its title as the ultimate instrument, they embarked on an exhilarating journey. Drawing inspiration from the masterpieces of legendary composers, songwriters, and performers over the last three centuries, they crafted a mesmerizing show that spans the spectrum from classical piano masterpieces to vibrant boogie-woogie, romantic ballads, and epic 80s synth battles in Piano Heist: Keys are the Champions! This enchanting experience unfolds as a delightful blend of theatrical magic, humour, audience engagement, touching narratives, a sprinkle of history, and an explosion of musical creativity. Tours have taken them across Canada and the Western U.S., captivating audiences with over 140 performances in both quaint towns and bustling cities.

title: Carnival of the Animals w/ Nashville Symphony
Celtic Spells
description: A new production by one of the founding members of Celtic Woman, GRAMMY and Emmy nominated artist and composer Máiréad Nesbitt returns to the stage with Celtic Spells. This storytelling performance with traditional Irish dance and music will take you on a journey to Ireland in the early 1900s when a young man meets a young woman, and an instant, soulful connection is made. The multi-instrumentalist Máiréad Nesbitt brings Irish heritage to life with her dynamic violin playing and promises an evening of enchanting music and storytelling.

title: The Philadelphia Orchestra
description: The world-renowned Philadelphia Orchestra strives to share the transformative power of music with the widest possible audience and to create joy, connection, and excitement through music in the Philadelphia region, across the country, and around the world. For their Bloomington performance, they'll be led by principal guest conductor Marin Alsop, a pioneering force in classical music and the first woman to serve as the head of major orchestras in the United States, South America, Austria, and Great Britain. Alsop will lead a program filled with brilliance and heart: Beethoven's Leonore Overture No. 3, a powerful tale of courage and triumph; Brahms's Variations on a Theme of Joseph Haydn, full of wit and wonder; and Schumann's radiant Symphony No. 2, music that soars with hope and resilience. Whether you're a longtime fan or new to orchestral music, this concert promises to captivate.

title: DEATH STRANDING Strands of Harmony World Tour
description: Embark on a journey to connect with fellow Porters through the power of music, and come together to celebrate the music of DEATH STRANDING live. Experience an orchestra and singers perform the most unforgettable songs from the series by Ludvig Forssell, Low Roar and other artists, while synchronized HD videos play on screen to relive Sam Porter Bridges' encounters, farewells, fierce battles, joys, and sorrows?allowing audiences to relive the stories of DEATH STRANDING and DEATH STRANDING 2: ON THE BEACH through music.

title: Video Games in Concert with Eimear Noone

title: Dolly Parton's Threads: My Songs in Symphony
description: TO PURCHASE ACCESSIBLE SEATING: VISIT ONLINE @ WWW.TICKETMASTER.COM OR WWW.LIVENATION.COM SUBJECT TO AVAILABILITY AND TICKET LIMITS ***PLEASE NOTE - PRESALES ARE ONLINE ONLY*** Dolly Parton brings her music to orchestras worldwide! Threads: My Songs In Symphony, is an innovative multimedia experience featuring Dolly on screen, leading audiences in a visual-musical journey of her songs, her life, and her stories. Accompanied by guest vocalists and musicians, audiences will hear new and innovative orchestrations of her hit songs, including ?Jolene,? ?Coat of Many Colors,? and ?I Will Always Love You,? in addition to her personal favorites and an as-yet unreleased selection from her upcoming Broadway musical. Co-produced by Dolly Parton together with Schirmer Theatrical and Sony Music Publishing. Dolly Parton is not present at this performance.

title: Serenade / Romance Rules
description: Sinfonia Toronto welcomes an exciting Italian guest conductor, Giovanni Pompeo, and welcomes back one of the orchestra's favourite piano soloists, Anya Alexeyev, to present a program of maximum Romantic melody. Anya stars as the soloist in an orchestral version of César Franck's luxurious Piano Quintet, and Maestro Pompeo leads the orchestra in one of the most beloved Romantic works in the entire repertoire, Tchaikovsky's famous Serenade.

title: THE EMPEROR / Beethoven - Shostakovich - Bach
description: Sinfonia Toronto wraps up their 2025-26 season with works of eternal genius. The superb young Toronto pianist Vanessa Yu joins the ensemble in one of the greatest concertos of all time, Beethoven's noble Piano Concerto No. 5, the "Emperor". Music Director Nurhan Arman leads the orchestra in Dmitri Shostakovich's poignant and personal Chamber Symphony in C minor Op. 110a and finishes with the powerful reassurance of J.S. Bach's Contrapunctus 1 and 2 in beautifully transparent orchestral versions.

title: Star Wars: Episode IV - A New Hope : Tucson Symphony Orchestra
description: Tucson Symphony Orchestra Matthew Kasper, conductor Luke Skywalker begins a journey that will change the galaxy. Nineteen years after the formation of the Empire, Luke is thrust into the struggle of the Rebel Alliance when he meets Obi-Wan Kenobi, who has lived for years in seclusion on the desert planet of Tatooine. Obi-Wan begins Luke's Jedi training as Luke joins him on a daring mission to rescue Rebel leader Princess Leia from the clutches of Darth Vader and the evil Empire. Don't miss this iconic film with John Williams' score performed live on stage by your TSO! Licensed by Disney Concerts
